===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|chin|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|ċinn||chin}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*kinnuz||chin}} (compare West Frisian/Dutch {{term|kin|lang=nl}}, Low German/German {{term|Kinn|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|kind|lang=da}}, Icelandic {{term|kinn|lang=is}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*ǵenHw-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*ǵnā(w)-||jaw}} (compare Welsh {{term|gen|lang=cy}}, Latin {{term|gena|lang=la}}, Tocharian A {{term|śanwem|lang=xto}}, Ancient Greek {{term|sc=polytonic|γένυς|tr=génus|lang=grc}} 'jaw', Armenian {{term|ծնոտ|tr=cnot|lang=hy|sc=Armn}}, Persian {{term|چانه|tr=čâne|sc=fa-Arab|lang=fa}}, Sanskrit {{term|हनु|tr=hánu|lang=sa|sc=Deva}}).

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# The bottom of a [[face]], especially, the lower [[jaw]] or the region below the [[mouth]].
# {{context|slang|US|lang=en}} talk.
# {{context|slang|British|lang=en}} A falsehood.
